30/12/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu on Wednesday (29 December) called for the depoliticalisation of the police. At the swearing-in ceremony of Administration and Home Affairs Minister Vasile Blaga, Basescu urged all police officers to abide by the law and pledged that during his administration, no politically motivated dismissals would be made. He added that he wants the police to serve the law, the public order and national interests, and urged more efforts against organised crime and corruption. (Rompres - 29/12/04)
